I'm in British Columbia, Canada, and like most places around here, we:
- Cannot go to social activities with more than 10 people
- All sport or recreational locations are closed until further notice
- The entire country is on a soft lockdown, which means nobody other than Canadian citizens can come into the country
- My school district has closed off the rest of the school year until further notice
- And most stores are empty of literally anything, but at least there's toilet paper
All in all, pretty bad.
